    <span>READ TIME: 4 min</span>
    <span>CATEGORY: Automation</span>
  </div>

  <h2>// What Make.com Can Automate on Shopify</h2>
  <p>
    Make.com connects to Shopify via an official integration that covers every major data type in your store. Order events, product changes, customer updates, inventory levels, and fulfilment status all trigger Make.com scenarios in real time. Here are the most common Shopify automations merchants build on Make.com's free plan:
  </p>

  <div class="use-cases">
    <div class="use-case">
      <div class="uc-category">ORDERS</div>
      <div class="uc-title">Order notification to Slack</div>
      <div class="uc-desc">New order → Send message to Slack channel with order details, items, and customer name.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="use-case">
      <div class="uc-category">INVENTORY</div>
      <div class="uc-title">Low stock alert</div>
      <div class="uc-desc">Inventory below threshold → Email or Slack alert with product name, variant, and current stock.</div>
      <div class="uc-saving">Replaces: $15–$49/month inventory alert apps</div>
    </div>
    <div class="use-case">
      <div class="uc-category">REPORTING</div>
      <div class="uc-title">Google Sheets order log</div>
      <div class="uc-desc">Every new order → New row in Google Sheet with order value, items, discount codes, customer data.</div>
      <div class="uc-saving">Replaces: $30–$60/month reporting apps</div>
    </div>
    <div class="use-case">
      <div class="uc-category">EMAIL</div>
      <div class="uc-title">Post-purchase flow trigger</div>
      <div class="uc-desc">Order fulfilled → Trigger email sequence in Systeme.io or GetResponse via webhook.</div>
      <div class="uc-saving">Replaces: Klaviyo post-purchase ($45+/month)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="use-case">
      <div class="uc-category">FULFILMENT</div>
      <div class="uc-title">Supplier purchase order</div>
      <div class="uc-desc">Inventory at reorder point → Create draft purchase order and email supplier automatically.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="use-case">
