      <tr><td>Shopify triggers</td><td class="win">100+</td><td>50+</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Native conditional logic</td><td class="win">Yes — routers, filters</td><td>Paid plans only</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Paid plan start</td><td class="win">$9/month (10,000 ops)</td><td>$19.99/month (750 tasks)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Visual scenario builder</td><td class="win">Yes — canvas interface</td><td>Linear list only</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="highlight-box">
    <div class="label">FREE PLAN USAGE TIP</div>
    <p style="margin:0; font-size:13px;">Make.com counts each individual action within a scenario as one operation. A 3-step scenario (Shopify order trigger → filter → Google Sheets row) uses 3 operations per run. At 1,000 operations/month free, that scenario can run approximately 333 times before you hit the limit — more than enough for stores processing under 300 orders per month.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>// Setting Up Shopify on Make.com</h2>
  <p>
    Connecting Shopify to Make.com requires OAuth authentication — no API keys or developer access needed. In Make.com, create a new scenario, add a Shopify module as the trigger, and click "Create a connection". You'll be redirected to your Shopify admin to authorise the integration. Once connected, all Shopify triggers and actions are immediately available. The full step-by-step walkthrough with pre-built templates for each automation above is in the <a href="/ultimate-shopify-automation-guide">Ultimate Shopify Automation Guide</a>.
  </p>

  <!-- FAQ ACCORDION -->
  <div class="faq-section">
    <h2>// Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Does Make.com work with Shopify Plus?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Yes. Make.com works identically with all Shopify plan levels including Basic, Shopify, Advanced, and Plus. The OAuth connection process is the same regardless of plan tier. Shopify Plus stores have access to additional API endpoints (like B2B and draft orders), which Make.com can also access via the Shopify modules.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">What happens if I exceed 1,000 operations on Make.com free?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Make.com pauses your scenarios when you hit the monthly operation limit until the next month's allowance resets. Active scenarios do not fail permanently — they simply stop processing until the reset. If you consistently exceed 1,000 operations, Make.com's Core plan at $9/month gives 10,000 operations — enough for most small Shopify stores.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Can Make.com trigger on Shopify abandoned carts?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Yes. Make.com has an "Abandoned Checkout Created" trigger in the Shopify module that fires when a customer starts checkout and does not complete it. You can use this trigger to send an abandoned cart recovery email via your email provider, add the customer to a Shopify customer list, or create a Slack notification. Shopify's native abandoned checkout recovery emails remain active in parallel — Make.com extends rather than replaces them.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Is Make.com reliable enough for critical Shopify operations?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Make.com is production-grade with 99.9% uptime SLA on paid plans. For critical operations like order fulfilment workflows, the paid Core plan ($9/month) is recommended as it includes priority execution and history logs. For non-critical automations like Slack notifications and Google Sheets logging, the free plan is reliable for everyday use.
      </div>
    </div>
